<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1807,1939]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,369,1807,1832]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Short description:</emphasis>
water bug with a flat, oval body and length between 8.5 and 
<quantity box="[1073,1153,1807,1831]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 mm</quantity>
(
<figureCitation box="[1169,1238,1807,1831]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1380,1403]" captionTargetBox="[197,1383,237,1298]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,193,1359]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 7. Aphelocheirus aestivalis. A) habitus; B) penis (ventral and lateral view); C) Left paramere (dorsal and lateral view); D) right paramere." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/203704/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Fig. 
<number box="[1223,1238,1807,1831]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
A). Colour: head, including antennae, yellowish, eyes blackish. Dorsally greyish thorax and abdomen, sometimes with broad yellowish lateral bands and yellowish marks in pronotum and abdomen. Yellow legs. Genitalia: both parameres with rounded heels (
<figureCitation box="[322,390,1915,1939]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1380,1403]" captionTargetBox="[197,1383,237,1298]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,193,1359]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 7. Aphelocheirus aestivalis. A) habitus; B) penis (ventral and lateral view); C) Left paramere (dorsal and lateral view); D) right paramere." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/203704/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Fig. 
<number box="[375,390,1915,1939]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
C,D). Penis with lateral spines in apical part (
<figureCitation box="[898,965,1915,1939]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1380,1403]" captionTargetBox="[197,1383,237,1298]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,193,1359]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 7. Aphelocheirus aestivalis. A) habitus; B) penis (ventral and lateral view); C) Left paramere (dorsal and lateral view); D) right paramere." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/203704/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Fig. 
<number box="[950,965,1915,1939]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
B).
</paragraph>
